</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="97" pageNumber="98" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="97.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[604,805,1194,1220]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Crested Bigscale</emphasis>
or Crested Ridgehead. To 
<quantity box="[1118,1189,1195,1221]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" unit="cm" value="19.0">19 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1207,1276,1194,1222]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.905" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" unit="in" value="7.5">7.5 in</quantity>
) SL (
<bibRefCitation author="Kotlyar" firstAuthor="Kotlyar" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" pagination="563 - 574" refId="ref292292" refString="Kotlyar, A. N. (2009) Revision of the genus Poromitra (Melamphaidae). Part 4. Species of P. cristiceps group: P. atlantica, P. oscitans, and P. agofonovae Kotlyar, species nova. Journal of Ichthyology, 49, 563 - 574. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / s 0032945209080013" type="journal article" year="2009">Kotlyar, 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Atlantic, Pacific, and Southern Oceans (
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke" box="[725,926,1231,1257]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Fricke" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" refId="ref280407" refString="Fricke, R., Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; van der Laan, R. (Eds). 2020. Eschmeyer's Catalog of Fishes: Genera, Species, Reference. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp (accessed 17 April 2021)." type="url" year="2020">
Fricke 
<emphasis box="[805,862,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
); western Pacific Ocean north to 
<collectingCountry box="[1303,1367,1231,1257]" name="Japan" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Fujii in 
<bibRefCitation author="Masuda" box="[230,460,1267,1293]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Masuda" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" refId="ref299291" refString="Masuda, H., Amaoka, K., Araga, C., Uyeno, T. &amp; Yoshino, T. (Eds). (1984) The Fishes of the Japanese Archipelago. Tokai University Press, Tokyo." type="book" year="1984">
Masuda 
<emphasis box="[330,390,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
1984
</bibRefCitation>
), and Russian north-western Pacific Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Orlov and Tokranov" box="[980,1284,1267,1293]" firstAuthor="Orlov" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" refId="ref307128" refString="Orlov, A. M. &amp; Tokranov, A. M. (2019) Checklist of deep-sea fishes of the Russian northwestern Pacific Ocean found at depths below 1000 m. Progress in Oceanography, 176, https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. pocean. 2019.102143" type="book" year="2019">Orlov and Tokranov 2019</bibRefCitation>
), to southern Bering Sea, and Gulf of Alaska (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[735,794,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
2002), to 
<collectingCountry box="[915,976,1303,1329]" name="Chile" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pequeno" box="[992,1160,1303,1329]" firstAuthor="Pequeno" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref311468" refString="Pequeno R., G. (1989) Peces de Chile lista sistematica revisada y comentada. Revista de Biologia Marina y Oceanografia, 24, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1989">Pequeño 1989</bibRefCitation>
). Primarily mesopelagic and bathypelagic; depth: 
<quantity box="[489,612,1339,1365]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" unit="m" value="2000.0" valueMax="4000.0" valueMin="0.0">0–4,000 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[629,736,1339,1366]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.998976" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" unit="ft" value="13120.0">13,120 ft</quantity>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Orlov and Tokranov" box="[763,1061,1339,1365]" firstAuthor="Orlov" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" refId="ref307128" refString="Orlov, A. M. &amp; Tokranov, A. M. (2019) Checklist of deep-sea fishes of the Russian northwestern Pacific Ocean found at depths below 1000 m. Progress in Oceanography, 176, https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. pocean. 2019.102143" type="book" year="2019">Orlov and Tokranov 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Considered a separate species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chapman, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[198,599,1375,1401]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Melamphaidae" genus="Poromitra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stephanoberyciformes" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis box="[198,397,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Poromitra rugosa</emphasis>
(Chapman, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
, by some authors. However, we follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Robertson" box="[1034,1290,1375,1401]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Robertson" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" pagination="1 - 125" refId="ref316855" refString="Robertson, D. R., Angulo, A., Baldwin, C. C., Pitassy, D., Driskell, A., Weigt, L. &amp; Navarro, I. J. F. (2017) Deep-water bony fishes collected by the B / O Miguel Oliver on the shelf edge of Pacific Central America: an annotated, illustrated and DNAbarcoded checklist. Zootaxa, 4348, 1 - 125. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4348.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">
Robertson 
<emphasis box="[1155,1210,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
and consider this 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[245,390,1411,1436]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Melamphaidae" genus="Poromitra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stephanoberyciformes" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassiceps">
<emphasis box="[245,390,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">P. crassiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was split into many taxa by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kotlyar" box="[862,1032,1411,1437]" firstAuthor="Kotlyar" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" pagination="563 - 574" refId="ref292292" refString="Kotlyar, A. N. (2009) Revision of the genus Poromitra (Melamphaidae). Part 4. Species of P. cristiceps group: P. atlantica, P. oscitans, and P. agofonovae Kotlyar, species nova. Journal of Ichthyology, 49, 563 - 574. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / s 0032945209080013" type="journal article" year="2009">Kotlyar (2009)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
